<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Fairness_Doctrine&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Further reading">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Further reading</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Fred_W._Friendly" title="Fred W. Friendly">Fred W. Friendly</a>, <i>The Good Guys, The Bad Guys and The First Amendment: free speech vs. fairness in broadcasting</i> (<a href="/wiki/Random_House" title="Random House">Random House</a>, New York, 1976; <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0394497252" class="internal">ISBN 0-394-49725-2</a>) — a history of the <i>Red Lion</i> case and the Fairness Doctrine.</li>
</ul>
